“The sea belongs to us”: Bolivia, enclosed by land, hopes that a court will open its way to the Pacific
Sailors patrol in front of the rope-decorated naval headquarters in La Paz.
There is a blue flag on public buildings.
Fleet bases from Lake Titicaca to the Amazon have the motto: “The sea is our legitimate property.
