New Cancer Vaccine May Teach the Immune System to “See” Degenerate Cells
A new cancer vaccine can teach the immune system to “see” and destroy degenerate cells.
The vaccine teaches the immune system to detect degenerate cells as part of the treatment.
The method is used to remove immune cells from a patient, which are altered in the laboratory.
These cells can “see” a common protein of many cancers and are then injected again.
A test vaccine shows promising results in patients with different cancers.
The ovarian cancer of a woman who was treated with the vaccine that teaches the immune system to detect degenerate cells disappeared for more than 18 months.
